summary:
Financial Controller with broad experience in all aspects ofaccounting, financial analysis & management, IT implementation to GO-LIVE oriented and semi-automated spreadsheet

Specialties: Play an active role with monthly and quarterly closings and assisting with US GAAP, IFRS and Financial Tool System; 
Analysis of consolidated monthly reporting, budget, forecast, and statutory accounts; 
Undertakings on various steps of the consolidation process within Group Entities; 
Financial Planning & Analysis, budgeting & forecasting; 
Multi-currency inter-company;
Develop automatic Excel using HFM (smartview), PeopleSoft & Oracle;
Manage the transaction flow from the invoicing sub-ledger to the general ledger;

profile_positions.description:
Country Finance Manager/Director at Americold Westland & Rotterdam (Jan 2023 – present)
• Lead all financial accounting, reporting activities, and the timely and accurate closing of accounts and preparation of periodic financial reports;
• Ensure compliance with all applicable accounting standards (US GAAP) and statutory accounting and reporting requirements in all relevant jurisdictions and that the financial accounting operations, documentation and reporting meet internal and external control requirements;
• Manage budgeting & forecasting processes, including full-year operating plans, quarterly forecasts and interim outlooks and create alignment across all levels of the organisation;
• Process improvement to all sectors that impact Revenue and EBITDA, including business operations, warehousing, outsourced labour, CAPEX projects, the billing process, unbilled revenue, sales accruals, bad debts, rebate issue, and business claims;
• Business control on the operational warehousing processes, including repacking, shipping, contractors, facilities, & planning that have impacts on accounting reporting requirements and identify potentials accounting risks;
• Assisting with SOX position papers and working proactively with external SOX auditors, financial controlling, and internal controlling to drive timely closure with sufficient quality of the audit requirements;
• Work closely with various finance teams (Group Financial Control, Group Internal Control, Group Accounting & Reporting, Regional Controlling, FP&A, and Tax);
• Deal proactively with external auditors (of the Company and Lenders), financial controlling, and internal controlling to drive timely closure with sufficient quality of the audit requirements and finalise the external financial statements.
• Leading and coaching the finance team;

Head of Group Treasury at Schiphol (Jun 2022 – Dec 2022)
• Responsible for managing the cashflow forecast reporting at a group and regional level;
• Maintaining and improving the cash pool (concentration) strategy for the EU and UK entities (SEPA and BACS payment);
• Responsible for the US reporting requirements related to the bank and entity information;
• Financial process related to (intercompany) debt, interest, cash, and intercompany balance reporting;
• Being the primary contact with HSBC (Bank) and maintaining the daily payment approval and users administration (access, payment & approval limit) and following up on urgent payments and insufficient funds;
• Responsible for the guarantee facility across EU entities and implementation of credit card compliance;
• Opening and closing the European bank accounts, including the UK;
• Dealing with the Trust company in Luxembourg for tax purposes;
• Supporting all entities for the bank, funding, credit card, and payment-related queries.

Annual Accounts, Monthly Management Report, Tax pack, DSO analysis, Rebates Acct, CIT & VAT, and Transfer Pricing;
• Liaise with the external Auditor & Tax to conduct the financial audit, PBC preparation, and audit follow-up;
• Quarterly/Yearly Securities and Exchange Commissions (SEC) reporting 10K and US GAAP reconciliations;
• Prepared journal entries in Oracles EBS and HFM, reviewed and approved accounting transactions (RNV) and GL account reconciliations (Assurenet);
• Led the month-end close call with EMEA HQ & FSS (Ireland) in explaining the movements;
• Conducted the quarterly T&E Concur compliance & WKR (werkkostenregeling). Provided the training for new joiners;
• Maintained control of Customer Services & Revenue Recognition accounting around complex contracts;
• Engaged with key stakeholder's Global End-to-End process PTP, RTR, OTC, and Payroll;
• Maintained the chart of accounts, cost centre/department structures, and an orderly accounting filing system;
• CBS reporting – Intrastat, ICL, ICV, Ziekteverzuim, Annual Wholesale report, etc.;
• Ad-hoc tasks include SAP implementation, Trial Balance Project), VAT adj, Cash Forecast, Dividend, and Bonus.

Responsible for managing the cashflows & financial covenants reporting at a group and regional level and improving the quality of the financial close relating to cash and net debt ratios;
Implemented the automatic weekly cash flow forecast for the US and EU region using Oracle smartview successfully;
Monitored and reported on the cash flow forecast and the cash requirement projections in combination with optimizing and maximizing the use of cash and capital funding; 
Implemented the new European cash pool and migrated the old banking system from Deutsche Bank to HSBC, including carrying out the KYC (Know Your Customer) process for all European sites;
Responsible for the consolidated quarterly Lenders & Equity Reporting, Compliance Certificate (1L first-lien debt & 2L second-lien debt) for US Bank & Morgan Stanley and Borrowing Based Certificate for Wells Fargo (US) and HSBC; 
Intercompany process across the Group's entities.
Reporting process improvements in FCCS (HFM Oracle) and Essbase (Smartview)

Manage the monthly closing and improve the the Group’s consolidation process and Statutory report – Dutch GAAP;
Take a lead to the preparation of Annual report and dealing with external auditor, engagement letter and audit fees;
Prepare the Group monthly management report by regions; Assist in the planning cycle process, which includes budget, long term plan and forecast consolidation;
Develop an automatic periodic intercompany matching process (from JetReport);
Dealing with clerical works such as clean-up the old intercompany balances for the past 4 years;
Transfer Pricing project – documentations, determining key allocations, cost allocation matrix & recharge process;
Cash management project – closing and opening bank accounts, cash pooling, sweep accounts, documentations etc;
Preparing the yearly report to the Dutch Central Bank (Dnb) for regulated entities;
Develop and maintain the mapping table for consolidation and management report; 
Work closely with CFO, external auditor and tax advisor;

Annual report (Dutch GAAP & US GAAP)
Group reporting (Switzerland) - monthly, quarterly, annual closing in US GAAP, statutory financial statements in Dutch GAAP;
Year-End Closings - Annual Reports, PBC audit list, Relationship with auditor – result: unqualified audit opinion;
Treasury accounting - involved in Bonds & Commercial Paper issuance and repayment process circa EUR 500M;
Group loans, Interest calculations incl. arrangement of loan agreements with BOD;
Tax accounting (APA ruling, 13L calculation, Deferred taxes, Group tax packages);
Dealing with external financial auditor, tax authorities & consultant and law firm;
Providing advice on PeopleSoft – ERP package;
Year-end audit;
Financial instruments, Bonds, Notes, Commercial Paper, Loans, Coupon etc;
Inter-company;
Managing Foreign & Dutch entities - legal documentations related.

Taking over financial activities for Alpinvest New York and Hongkong subsidiaries;
Month/Quarter/Year-end financial close;
US GAAP;
Project costing, Billing report US Holdings;
Peoplesoft; ARM System (Hyperion Account Reconciliation Manager), Infor, Concur, HFM, Smartview;
